  "prompt": "What's the average number of answers to each question on Quora?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Quora has not publicly disclosed specific statistics regarding the average number of answers per question. The number of answers a question receives on Quora can vary widely based on several factors, including:\n\n1. **Topic Popularity:** Questions on widely appealing or trending topics tend to attract more answers. For example, questions related to technology, personal development, or current events often receive numerous responses.\n\n2. **Question Specificity:** More general questions may attract a higher number of answers as they are open to diverse perspectives, whereas highly specific or niche questions might receive fewer responses.\n\n3. **User Engagement:** The level of engagement within different Quora communities or topics can influence how many answers a question garners. Active communities tend to generate more interactions, including answers.\n\n4. **Timing and Visibility:** Questions that gain visibility quickly\u2014either through shares, upvotes, or being featured\u2014are more likely to receive multiple answers.\n\nWhile some questions on Quora receive just a handful of answers, others, especially those that resonate with a large audience, can attract dozens or even hundreds of responses. If you're interested in more precise or updated statistics, you might consider reaching out directly to Quora through their [official support channels](https://help.quora.com/) or reviewing any publicly available reports or press releases they may have issued.",
